"id": 89971}, {"id": 89972}, {"id": 89973}, {"id": 89974}, {"id": 90026}, {"id": 90121}, {"id": 90217}, {"id": 90416}, {"id": 91538}, {"id": 91648}, {"id": 91649}, {"id": 91650}, {"id": 91651}, {"id": 91652}, {"id": 91721}, {"id": 92273}, {"id": 98171}, {"id": 105531}, {"id": 105532}, {"id": 105533}, {"id": 105534}, {"id": 105535}, {"id": 105549}, {"id": 105556}, {"id": 105557}, {"id": 105558}, {"id": 107835}, {"id": 107903}, {"id": 107953}, {"id": 111066}, {"id": 111154}, {"id": 112349}, {"id": 114172}, {"id": 114173}, {"id": 114328}, {"id": 116038}, {"id": 116868}, {"id": 119617}, {"id": 120896}, {"id": 121302}, {"id": 127898}, {"id": 127911}, {"id": 127913}, {"id": 128051}, {"id": 128052}, {"id": 128228}, {"id": 128252}, {"id": 128290}, {"id": 128298}, {"id": 128344}, {"id": 128345}, {"id": 128346}, {"id": 128591}, {"id": 128592}, {"id": 128593}, {"id": 128828}, {"id": 129347}, {"id": 129551}, {"id": 130058}, {"id": 131671}, {"id": 131672}, {"id": 131673}, {"id": 131674}, {"id": 131675}, {"id": 134083}, {"id": 137776}, {"id": 137780}, {"id": 138484}, {"id": 140723}, {"id": 140724}]', '[{"id": 55883}, {"id": 56090}, {"id": 55712}, {"id": 56571}, {"id": 40617}, {"id": 40993}, {"id": 55803}, {"id": 56010}, {"id": 56433}, {"id": 56591}]', '1321', '<p>Four Color Comics (or just Four Color) is a series that ran from 1942 and ended in 1962. It is known that the series had well over 1,000 issues, but the precise number of original issues has not been determined due to skipped issues and reprints. The series finally came to an end with Issue #1354 and so at the moment the series holds the record for having the most issues published of any American comic book series, as its nearest rivals have recently been cancelled for the sake of a relaunch (with only <a href="/action-comics/4050-18005/" data-ref-id="4050-18005">Action Comics</a> ever surpassing 900 issues). The series is surpassed in length by many other European comics.</p><p><b>List of Unpublished Issues</b></p><ul><li>1217</li><li>1228</li><li>1277</li><li>1292</li><li>1314-1327</li><li>1329</li><li>1331</li><li>1334</li><li>1338-1340</li><li>1342-1347</li><li>1351-1353</li></ul><p>Unlike most comics, the title found in Four Color''s indicia change nearly every issue to reflect the title found on the cover. For example, <a href="/four-color-mister-ed-the-talking-horse/4000-90288/" data-ref-id="4000-90288">Four Color #1295</a>, which features the television character <a href="/mister-ed/4005-67764/" data-ref-id="4005-67764">Mister Ed</a>, is listed in the indicia as "Mister Ed, the Talking Horse #1295," even though none of the previous issues featured Mister Ed. To avoid confusion, the titles of the comics for this series will be that found in the indicia.</p><h4>Reprints (single issues)</h4><ul><li><a href="/brave-eagle/4050-113113/" data-ref-id="4050-113113">Brave Eagle</a> #1-5 (#705, 770, 816, 879, 929)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-new-adventures-of-sherlock-holmes/4050-113378/">The New Adventures of Sherlock Holmes</a> #1-2 (#1169, 1245)</li><li><a href="/santa-claus-funnies/4050-37890/" data-ref-id="4050-37890">Santa Claus Funnies</a> #1-7 (#61, 91, 128, 175, 205, 254, 302)</li><li><a href="/wagon-train/4050-113130/" data-ref-id="4050-113130">Wagon Train</a> #1-3 (#895, 971, 1019)</li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1949-a-john-buscema-western-tr/4000-682225/">A John Buscema Western Treasury</a> (#927, 1077, 1130)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-406-a-mr-magoo-treasury-volume/4000-680354/">A Mr. Magoo Treasury: Volume 1</a> (#561, 602)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-443-a-mr-magoo-treasury-volume/4000-680355/">A Mr. Magoo Treasury: Volume 2</a> (#1235)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-332-a-zane-greys-king-of-the-r/4000-681082/">A Zane Grey''s King of the Royal Mounted Treasury: Volume 1</a> (#207, 265, 283, 384, 935)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1995-a-zane-greys-king-of-the-/4000-683993/">A Zane Grey''s King of the Royal Mounted Treasury: Volume 2</a> (#310, 340, 363)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-673-the-complete-tom-corbett-s/4000-681271/">The Complete Tom Corbett: Space Cadet - Volume 1</a> (#378, 400, 421)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-6731172-the-complete-tom-corbe/4000-684791/">The Complete Tom Corbett: Space Cadet Giant</a> (#378, 400, 421)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-521-the-complete-wagon-train/4000-682451/">The Complete Wagon Train</a> (#895, 971, 1019)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1623-hercules-unchained/4000-680796/">Hercules Unchained</a> (#1006, 1121)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/pre-code-classics-tom-corbett-space-cadet-1-volume/4000-594217/" data-ref-id="4000-594217">Pre-Code Classics Tom Corbett: Space Cadet Volume One</a> (#378, 400 &amp; 421)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-799-sea-hunt-volume-1/4000-681347/">Sea Hunt: Volume 1</a> (#928, 994, 1041)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-799949-sea-hunt-volumes-1-and-/4000-683097/">Sea Hunt: Volumes 1 &amp; 2</a> (#928, 994, 1041)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1060-sherlock-holmes/4000-684298/">Sherlock Holmes</a> (#1169, 1245)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1141-tv-western-heroes-volume-/4000-680766/">TV Western Heroes: Volume 1</a> (#860, 880, 895, 934, 1009, 1013, 1023, 1035, 1125, 1225)</li></ul>', '927', 'Four Color', '1942', '84997', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/11/119838/2827033-fourcolor1.jpg', '4');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 40362}, {"id": 25992}, {"id": 77281}, {"id": 40372}, {"id": 40370}, {"id": 40364}, {"id": 91587}, {"id": 25994}, {"id": 24033}, {"id": 9671}, {"id": 40367}, {"id": 40368}, {"id": 9793}, {"id": 6647}, {"id": 39871}, {"id": 40373}, {"id": 63206}, {"id": 74611}, {"id": 40375}, {"id": 62974}, {"id": 67267}, {"id": 195981}, {"id": 82789}, {"id": 82807}, {"id": 85122}, {"id": 91588}, {"id": 109718}, {"id": 164818}, {"id": 177243}, {"id": 3049}, {"id": 40371}, {"id": 39874}, {"id": 37554}, {"id": 35568}, {"id": 31333}, {"id": 25780}, {"id": 19824}, {"id": 14338}, {"id": 14336}, {"id": 13907}, {"id": 10691}, {"id": 9829}, {"id": 8153}, {"id": 6079}, {"id": 4305}, {"id": 3099}]', '[{"id": 42382}]', '117', '<p>Continues from <a href="/captain-battle-jr/4050-7412/" data-ref-id="4050-7412">Captain Battle</a><a href="/captain-battle-jr/4050-7412/" data-ref-id="4050-7412"> Jr</a>.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1156-the-complete-crimebuster-/4000-681503/">The Complete Crimebuster: Volume 1</a> (Crimebuster stories from #3-18)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1276-a-golden-age-space-opera-/4000-680888/">A Golden Age Space Opera Special</a> (Rocky X vs The Claw from #89-93)</li></ul>', '942', 'Boy Comics', '1942', '168950', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/2/27783/937979-boy_1.jpg', '52');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 9436}, {"id": 121713}, {"id": 130307}, {"id": 12954}, {"id": 32248}, {"id": 75952}, {"id": 173532}, {"id": 146432}, {"id": 108243}, {"id": 108242}, {"id": 108241}, {"id": 79485}, {"id": 76617}, {"id": 39610}, {"id": 33954}, {"id": 32725}, {"id": 12898}, {"id": 12115}, {"id": 12112}]', '[{"id": 58592}]', '126', '<h4><span>Publishing History</span></h4><ul><li>(#1-21) <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/silver-streak-comics/4050-25365/">Silver Streak Comics</a>.</li><li>(#22-147) Crime Does Not Pay (#22 = Jul, 1942)</li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-143-crime-does-not-pay-62-66/4000-680996/">Crime Does Not Pay #62-66</a>.</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-144-crime-does-not-pay-67-71/4000-680997/">Crime Does Not Pay #67-71</a>.</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-145-crime-does-not-pay-72-76/4000-680998/">Crime Does Not Pay #72-76</a>.</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-146-crime-does-not-pay-77-81/4000-680999/">Crime Does Not Pay #77-81</a>.</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-147-crime-does-not-pay-82-86/4000-681000/">Crime Does Not Pay #82-86</a>.</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-148-crime-does-not-pay-87-91/4000-681001/">Crime Does Not Pay #87-91</a>.</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-149-crime-does-not-pay-92-96/4000-681002/">Crime Does Not Pay #92-96</a>.</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-150-crime-does-not-pay-97-101/4000-681003/">Crime Does Not Pay #97-101</a>.</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-151-crime-does-not-pay-102-107/4000-681004/">Crime Does Not Pay #102-107</a>.</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-152-crime-does-not-pay-108-115/4000-681005/">Crime Does Not Pay #108-115</a>.</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-153-crime-does-not-pay-116-123/4000-681006/">Crime Does Not Pay #116-123</a>.</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-154-crime-does-not-pay-124-131/4000-681007/">Crime Does Not Pay #124-131</a>.</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-155-crime-does-not-pay-132-139/4000-681008/">Crime Does Not Pay #132-139</a>.</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-156-crime-does-not-pay-140-147/4000-681009/">Crime Does Not Pay #140-147</a>.</li><li><a href="/crime-does-not-pay-archives-vol-1/4000-321570/" data-ref-id="4000-321570">Crime Does Not Pay Archives vol. 1</a> (#22-25)</li><li><a href="/crime-does-not-pay-archives-vol-2/4000-344053/" data-ref-id="4000-344053">Crime Does Not Pay Archives vol. 2</a> (#26-29)</li><li><a href="/crime-does-not-pay-archives-vol-3/4000-370253/" data-ref-id="4000-370253">Crime Does Not Pay Archives vol. 3</a> (#30-33)</li><li><a href="/crime-does-not-pay-archives-vol-4/4000-392336/" data-ref-id="4000-392336">Crime Does Not Pay Archives vol. 4</a> (#34-37)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/crime-does-not-pay-archives-5-volume-5/4000-423651/" data-ref-id="4000-423651">Crime Does Not Pay Archives vol. 5</a> (#38-41)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/crime-does-not-pay-archives-6-volume-6/4000-435023/" data-ref-id="4000-435023">Crime Does Not Pay Archives vol. 6</a> (#42-45)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/crime-does-not-pay-archives-7-volume-7/4000-450533/" data-ref-id="4000-450533">Crime Does Not Pay Archives vol. 7</a> (#46-49)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/crime-does-not-pay-archives-8-volume-8/4000-467620/" data-ref-id="4000-467620">Crime Does Not Pay Archives vol. 8</a> (#50-53)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1287-werthams-weapons-volume-1/4000-681631/">Wertham''s Weapons: Volume 1</a> (#63)</li></ul>', '943', 'Crime Does Not Pay', '1942', '180169', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/9116/1011229-22.jpg', '52');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 55068}, {"id": 55082}, {"id": 55078}, {"id": 46860}, {"id": 190641}, {"id": 92373}, {"id": 55080}, {"id": 55079}, {"id": 52878}, {"id": 47203}, {"id": 5585}, {"id": 46271}, {"id": 33721}, {"id": 22006}, {"id": 14422}, {"id": 13743}, {"id": 9671}, {"id": 9379}, {"id": 7620}]', 'NaN', '26', '<p>Comedy Comics was an anthology published during the 1940''s, beginning with #9 (the first eight issues were published in the superhero title <a data-ref-id="4050-19070" href="/daring-mystery-comics/4050-19070/" slug="daring-mystery-comics">Daring Mystery Comics</a>), by its sixth issue the comic began to feature Super Rabbit (who starred in several 1940''s Timely Comics). As World War II was going on at the time, he would of course occasionally defeat Nazis although he would also stop regular criminals. After holding onto the title for twenty issues (and four years), with #34, Margie became the feature and with #35 the series changed its name to reflect this, becoming <a data-ref-id="4050-1113" href="/margie-comics/4050-1113/" slug="margie-comics">Margie Comics</a>.</p>', '944', 'Comedy Comics', '1942', '139049', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/229/546927-1.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 55075}, {"id": 55076}, {"id": 55077}, {"id": 173149}, {"id": 173152}, {"id": 173153}, {"id": 173151}, {"id": 173155}, {"id": 143420}, {"id": 173150}, {"id": 68019}, {"id": 55068}, {"id": 83151}, {"id": 173154}]', 'NaN', '26', '<p>After issue 15 the series continued as <a data-ref-id="4050-1006" href="/funny-tunes/4050-1006/" slug="funny-tunes">     Funny Tunes</a> and then resumes again at 16 without a break in the sequence. The series then continued as <a data-ref-id="4050-1141" href="/cindy-comics/4050-1141/" slug="cindy-comics">    Cindy Comics</a> (27-38) for 12 issues, <a data-ref-id="4050-1346" href="/cindy-smith/4050-1346/" slug="cindy-smith">   Cindy Smith</a> (39-40) for 2 issues, finally into <a data-ref-id="4050-30425" href="/crime-cant-win/4050-30425/" slug="crime-cant-win">  Crime Can''t Win</a> 41(1)-12.</p>', '946', 'Krazy Komics', '1942', '94875', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/61880-946-94875-1-krazy-komics.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 3104}, {"id": 3105}, {"id": 85130}, {"id": 55081}, {"id": 173160}, {"id": 173159}, {"id": 85847}, {"id": 173157}, {"id": 39433}, {"id": 173156}, {"id": 9675}, {"id": 173158}, {"id": 1951}, {"id": 1950}, {"id": 9676}, {"id": 39434}, {"id": 123200}, {"id": 184356}, {"id": 1442}, {"id": 81865}, {"id": 167327}, {"id": 171377}, {"id": 82002}, {"id": 64424}, {"id": 13779}, {"id": 167363}, {"id": 31595}, {"id": 16852}, {"id": 143420}, {"id": 55075}, {"id": 167328}, {"id": 40470}, {"id": 173149}, {"id": 9673}, {"id": 9672}, {"id": 9671}, {"id": 9624}, {"id": 3115}, {"id": 55077}]', 'NaN', '83', '<p>Issues #84-86 are in <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/paul-terrys-terrytoon-comics/4050-135044/">Paul Terry''s Terrytoon Comics</a> volume.</p>', '948', 'Terry-Toons Comics', '1942', '160040', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/2/27783/836240-terrytoon_1.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 10935}, {"id": 168081}, {"id": 174412}, {"id": 174632}, {"id": 170063}, {"id": 68176}, {"id": 40252}, {"id": 40249}, {"id": 6263}, {"id": 24925}, {"id": 2350}, {"id": 9671}, {"id": 54347}, {"id": 52973}, {"id": 137968}, {"id": 175516}, {"id": 166849}, {"id": 174234}, {"id": 40251}, {"id": 173161}, {"id": 173802}, {"id": 173809}, {"id": 173810}, {"id": 2365}, {"id": 77583}, {"id": 170321}, {"id": 53004}, {"id": 171472}, {"id": 115718}, {"id": 42583}, {"id": 77578}, {"id": 138986}, {"id": 139125}, {"id": 139131}, {"id": 173555}, {"id": 32770}, {"id": 32592}, {"id": 168202}, {"id": 24740}, {"id": 24664}, {"id": 21893}, {"id": 10619}, {"id": 14921}, {"id": 168389}, {"id": 168272}, {"id": 168390}, {"id": 180590}, {"id": 170612}, {"id": 180589}, {"id": 171849}, {"id": 172231}, {"id": 172232}, {"id": 180494}, {"id": 180397}, {"id": 172283}, {"id": 173556}, {"id": 174411}, {"id": 179019}, {"id": 175402}, {"id": 36673}, {"id": 2356}, {"id": 6079}, {"id": 8153}, {"id": 9236}, {"id": 9672}, {"id": 14335}, {"id": 16890}, {"id": 21095}, {"id": 22143}, {"id": 29642}, {"id": 31684}, {"id": 31685}, {"id": 35568}, {"id": 36452}, {"id": 168201}, {"id": 37303}, {"id": 40078}, {"id": 40079}, {"id": 45741}, {"id": 54348}, {"id": 62053}, {"id": 63244}, {"id": 75160}, {"id": 99811}, {"id": 115733}, {"id": 137969}, {"id": 138660}, {"id": 160345}, {"id": 164821}]', '[{"id": 43734}]', '118', '<p>#34 does not exist, rather the issue with 35 on the cover says 34 on the interior.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1573-the-golden-age-captain-ma/4000-680805/">The Golden Age Captain Marvel Jr.: Volume 12</a> (#51-55)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1574-the-golden-age-captain-ma/4000-680801/">The Golden Age Captain Marvel Jr.: Volume 13</a> (56-60)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1575-the-golden-age-captain-ma/4000-680800/">The Golden Age Captain Marvel Jr.: Volume 14</a> (#61-65)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-2053-golden-age-captain-marvel/4000-685506/">Golden Age Captain Marvel Jr. Giant #3</a> (#10-21)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-2068-mac-raboys-captain-marvel/4000-680748/">Mac Raboy''s Captain Marvel Jr. Album: Volume 1</a> (#1-25)</li></ul>', '953', 'Captain Marvel, Jr.', '1942', '152984', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/5/58127/1768831-captain_marvel_jr._vol_1_1.jpg', '34');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 55068}, {"id": 55075}, {"id": 55076}, {"id": 68019}, {"id": 55082}, {"id": 83151}]', 'NaN', '12', '<p>All Surprise ran during 1943 through 1946 for 12 issues. This series then continued into <a data-ref-id="4050-1143" href="/jeanie-comics/4050-1143/" slug="jeanie-comics"> Jeanie Comics</a>.</p>', '972', 'All Surprise Comics', '1943', '56959', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/47575-972-56959-1-all-surprise.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 9236}, {"id": 27871}, {"id": 115733}, {"id": 2350}]', '[{"id": 55883}]', '69', '<p>Don Winslow of the Navy was originally a comic strip (debuting on March 5, 1934) and while several comics would reprint the strips in the 30''s and 40''s, Fawcett launched this series in 1943 featuring the publication of original Don Winslow stories in the common anthology style of numerous short stories, the majority of which focused on Don Winslow. The strip was intended to excite kids about life in the military, hopefully leading them to later seek a place in the US Armed Forces. Fawcett''s comic lasted up until 1948 when it ceased publication after sixty-four issues. The book would later see two brief revivals before it ended; the first was in 1951 when Fawcett briefly resurrected the series for five more issues, the second came in 1955 when Charlton printed reprints of the series but this only lasted for four issues and after that the title''s compiled numbering was continued in the Charlton series, <a href="/fightin-navy/4050-36532/" data-ref-id="4050-36532">Fightin'' Navy</a>.</p><h4>Publishers</h4><ul><li>#01-69: <a href="/fawcett-publications/4010-34/" data-ref-id="4010-34">Fawcett Publications</a></li><li>Issues #70-73 are published under <a href="/charlton/4010-125/" data-ref-id="4010-125">Charlton</a>, with a volume name <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/don-winslow/4050-144181/">Don Winslow</a>.</li></ul><h4>Collected Edition</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1272-the-complete-singapore-sa/4000-680834/">The Complete Singapore Sal</a> (SS stories from #47, 51, 57 and 60)</li></ul>', '978', 'Don Winslow of the Navy', '1943', '92218', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/59223-978-92218-1-don-winslow-of-the-n.jpg', '34');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 3849}, {"id": 56085}, {"id": 7290}, {"id": 7291}, {"id": 7295}, {"id": 7296}, {"id": 7305}, {"id": 26821}, {"id": 34058}, {"id": 44064}, {"id": 44340}, {"id": 128582}]', 'NaN', '3', '<p><b>Publishers</b></p><p>#1-2: DC Comics</p><p>#3: EC</p><p>The Bible has heroes, villains, and amazing feats, so its content proved well suited to the comic medium. The first DC series to feature biblical tales had appeared in 1942. Titled Picture Stories from the Bible, it had adapted stories from the Old Testament including those of Moses, Abraham, the prophet Elijah and the famous David and Goliath. The 1944 version, labeled "New Testament Edition" on the cover, told tales from the life of Christ. Don Cameron illustrated the series, which offered 45pages of religious education for just 10c.</p>', '988', 'Picture Stories from the Bible (New Testament)', '1944', '94364', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/61369-988-94364-1-picture-stories-from.jpg', '10');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 55075}, {"id": 55076}, {"id": 55068}, {"id": 55082}]', 'NaN', '6', '<p>Comic Capers was an anthology series featuring anthropomorphic animal characters such as Ziggy Pig, Silly Seal and Super Rabbit that ran from 1944-1946 at a seasonal publishing rate, lasting a total of six issues. The featured characters in the series also had their own titles published alongside it: <a data-ref-id="4050-1013" href="/ziggy-pig-silly-seal-comics/4050-1013/" slug="ziggy-pig-silly-seal-comics">Ziggy Pig-Silly Seal Comics</a> and <a data-ref-id="4050-32169" href="/super-rabbit/4050-32169/" slug="super-rabbit">Super Rabbit</a>.</p>', '1003', 'Comic Capers', '1944', '188262', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/5/54649/1063482-comic_capers_1.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 55075}, {"id": 55076}, {"id": 55077}]', 'NaN', '8', '<p> Funny Tunes numbers from 16 to 23 for a total of 8 issues. Series numbering continued from <a data-ref-id="4050-946" href="/krazy-komics/4050-946/" slug="krazy-komics">  Krazy Komics</a> and continues into <a data-ref-id="4050-1146" href="/oscar-comics/4050-1146/" slug="oscar-comics"> Oscar Comics</a> with issues 24(1) </p>', '1006', 'Funny Tunes', '1944', '90746', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/57751-1006-90746-1-funny-tunes.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 55068}, {"id": 55075}, {"id": 55076}, {"id": 55082}]', 'NaN', '4', '<p>Ideal Comics ran during 1944 through 1946 for 4 issues. This series then continued into Willie Comics. </p>', '1007', 'Ideal Comics', '1944', '90857', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/57862-1007-90857-1-ideal-comics.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 9375}, {"id": 169135}, {"id": 18526}, {"id": 178093}, {"id": 7626}, {"id": 7629}, {"id": 9376}, {"id": 7628}, {"id": 127180}, {"id": 9379}, {"id": 40110}, {"id": 68014}, {"id": 127226}, {"id": 190641}]', 'NaN', '23', '<p>Tessie the Typist was an ongoing romance/humor anthology published by Marvel in the forties, from 1944-1949 for twenty-three issues. It was the first of its class. The numbering was then continued in <a href="/tiny-tessie/4050-30496/" data-ref-id="4050-30496">Tiny Tessie</a> for a single issue and <a href="/real-experiences/4050-30475/" data-ref-id="4050-30475">Real Experiences</a> for another issue.</p><p>Tessie the Typist starred the typist of the same name, a temperamental and eccentric character that appeared in <a href="/joker-comics/4050-27160/" data-ref-id="4050-27160">Joker Comics</a> before, being the more popular character in the magazine. She was accompained by her boyfriend Skidsy, who had to suffer her antics.</p><p>Despite her early popularity, Tessie was one of the less-successful books of its kind, longer running comics featuring other girls included: <a href="/millie-the-model/4050-19441/" data-ref-id="4050-19441">Millie the Model</a>, <a href="/hedy-de-vine-comics/4050-1142/" data-ref-id="4050-1142">Hedy De Vine</a>/<a href="/hedy-of-hollywood-comics/4050-1353/" data-ref-id="4050-1353">Hedy of Hollywood</a>, <a href="/nellie-the-nurse/4050-1061/" data-ref-id="4050-1061">Nellie the Nurse</a> and <a href="/patsy-walker/4050-1062/" data-ref-id="4050-1062">Patsy Walker</a>. All of them followed the formula and conventions that made Tessie popular in the first place.</p>', '1012', 'Tessie the Typist', '1944', '167732', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/9116/927188-1.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 55075}, {"id": 55076}, {"id": 38840}, {"id": 55077}, {"id": 55082}]', 'NaN', '6', '<p>Ziggy Pig And Silly Seal Comics ran during 1944 through 1946 for 6 issues.</p>', '1013', 'Ziggy Pig-Silly Seal Comics', '1944', '57855', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/48383-1013-57855-1-ziggy-pig-and-silly-.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 5652}, {"id": 1346}, {"id": 4210}, {"id": 1345}, {"id": 25401}, {"id": 5151}, {"id": 53083}, {"id": 83668}, {"id": 77460}, {"id": 179274}, {"id": 5140}, {"id": 5142}, {"id": 5148}, {"id": 5146}, {"id": 74467}, {"id": 5143}, {"id": 3071}, {"id": 5139}, {"id": 75928}, {"id": 36175}, {"id": 5154}, {"id": 129623}, {"id": 123238}, {"id": 33503}, {"id": 179276}, {"id": 12112}, {"id": 179284}, {"id": 5155}, {"id": 5152}, {"id": 5147}, {"id": 83667}, {"id": 3072}, {"id": 3070}, {"id": 123237}, {"id": 39296}, {"id": 68094}, {"id": 39135}, {"id": 5180}, {"id": 25901}, {"id": 5162}, {"id": 5137}, {"id": 5160}, {"id": 5153}, {"id": 32725}, {"id": 5144}, {"id": 110274}, {"id": 103997}, {"id": 191609}, {"id": 191608}, {"id": 189192}, {"id": 103998}, {"id": 103999}, {"id": 180796}, {"id": 179286}, {"id": 126960}, {"id": 131209}, {"id": 166774}, {"id": 192135}, {"id": 178673}, {"id": 38840}, {"id": 1838}, {"id": 3085}, {"id": 5132}, {"id": 5136}, {"id": 5149}, {"id": 5150}, {"id": 5168}, {"id": 20237}, {"id": 22143}, {"id": 103996}, {"id": 39606}, {"id": 44940}, {"id": 47989}, {"id": 48315}, {"id": 48858}, {"id": 51672}, {"id": 52544}, {"id": 70035}, {"id": 72194}]', '[{"id": 56432}]', '139', '<figure data-align="right" data-size="medium" data-img-src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/15776/8677434-a-1comicsindicia.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-8677434" data-ratio="0.41904761904762" data-width="315" data-embed-type="image" style="width: 315px"><a class="fluid-height" style="padding-bottom:41.9%" href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/15776/8677434-a-1comicsindicia.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-8677434"><img alt="No Caption Provided" src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/15776/8677434-a-1comicsindicia.jpg" srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/15776/8677434-a-1comicsindicia.jpg 315w" sizes="(max-width: 315px) 100vw, 315px" data-width="315"></a></figure><p>The volume started with the main numbering following A-1 Comics name. From Issue #4 the issue name was sometimes used in the brackets. From Issue #17, the issue name was put in the front and A-1 issue number in the brackets.</p>', '1032', 'A-1 Comics', '1944', '102943', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/66021-1032-99018-1-a-1-comics.jpg', '84');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 9375}, {"id": 18526}, {"id": 7626}, {"id": 5585}, {"id": 7629}, {"id": 190641}, {"id": 9379}, {"id": 9376}, {"id": 7628}, {"id": 68014}, {"id": 127180}, {"id": 178093}, {"id": 169135}, {"id": 127226}, {"id": 9382}, {"id": 9383}, {"id": 9384}, {"id": 3316}]', 'NaN', '23', '<p>Gay Comics was an anthology in the 1940''s by Marvel''s publishing predecessor Timely featuring such characters as Millie the Model, Tessie the Typist and Nellie the Nurse. Although <a data-ref-id="4050-30453" href="/gay-comics/4050-30453/" slug="gay-comics">Gay Comics</a> #1 was released earlier in the year (as its own volume), this series began with #18 with no clue as to where the first seventeen issues came from. Gay Comics then continued for twenty-three issues until it ended with #40, continuing it''s numbering in <a data-ref-id="4050-30458" href="/honeymoon/4050-30458/" slug="honeymoon">Honeymoon</a> #41.</p>', '1038', 'Gay Comics', '1944', '92191', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/59196-1038-92191-1-gay-comics.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 50397}, {"id": 50396}, {"id": 24902}, {"id": 36452}, {"id": 5634}, {"id": 14131}, {"id": 38634}, {"id": 38759}, {"id": 44015}, {"id": 39976}, {"id": 39875}, {"id": 39874}, {"id": 39871}, {"id": 39453}, {"id": 38760}, {"id": 51237}, {"id": 38758}, {"id": 37708}, {"id": 37330}, {"id": 36038}, {"id": 31692}, {"id": 31251}, {"id": 76718}, {"id": 93564}, {"id": 89511}, {"id": 89510}, {"id": 87919}, {"id": 84883}, {"id": 76728}, {"id": 76724}, {"id": 76723}, {"id": 76719}, {"id": 28496}, {"id": 76715}, {"id": 76711}, {"id": 76710}, {"id": 67377}, {"id": 65440}, {"id": 62772}, {"id": 62768}, {"id": 62679}, {"id": 55179}, {"id": 6073}, {"id": 9628}, {"id": 9622}, {"id": 8753}, {"id": 8650}, {"id": 8156}, {"id": 8155}, {"id": 8154}, {"id": 8153}, {"id": 6074}, {"id": 9773}, {"id": 5636}, {"id": 5635}, {"id": 4534}, {"id": 3941}, {"id": 3940}, {"id": 3888}, {"id": 3854}, {"id": 3049}, {"id": 16776}, {"id": 1369}, {"id": 22924}, {"id": 22788}, {"id": 19712}, {"id": 19699}, {"id": 19698}, {"id": 19697}, {"id": 19192}, {"id": 18113}, {"id": 28769}, {"id": 14295}, {"id": 14293}, {"id": 14292}, {"id": 12142}, {"id": 12119}, {"id": 12026}, {"id": 11784}, {"id": 10735}]', 'NaN', '4', NULL, '1041', 'Picture Stories from American History', '1945', '94360', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/61365-1041-94360-1-picture-stories-from.jpg', '89');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 16383}, {"id": 67873}, {"id": 16385}, {"id": 16386}, {"id": 16368}, {"id": 16363}, {"id": 1807}, {"id": 137394}, {"id": 16246}, {"id": 16890}, {"id": 16384}, {"id": 18060}, {"id": 16388}, {"id": 63266}, {"id": 29322}, {"id": 160345}, {"id": 177932}, {"id": 16871}, {"id": 16412}, {"id": 16393}, {"id": 16387}, {"id": 9634}, {"id": 6890}, {"id": 5936}]', 'NaN', '127', '<p>Real Screen Comics was an anthology series published by DC from 1945 to 1959 over the course of 127 issues. Featured throughout the series run were the characters The Fox and The Crow and although they were the main feature, other stories were published in the series as well including "Flippity and Flop" and "Tito and His Burrito". The series title is a reference to "Screen Gems" the animation studio that existed from 1940-1946 wherein characters like those featured in the aforementioned comics originally came into being through the form of cartoons.</p><p><b>General Notes</b></p><p>Real Screen <i>Comics</i> #1 does not exist, for the first issue, see <a data-ref-id="4050-20851" href="/real-screen-funnies/4050-20851/" slug="real-screen-funnies">Real Screen Funnies</a>.</p><p>After #128, the series changed its name to <a data-ref-id="4050-1997" href="/tv-screen-cartoons/4050-1997/" slug="tv-screen-cartoons">TV Screen Cartoons</a> under which it lasted for another ten issues.</p>', '1043', 'Real Screen Comics', '1945', '56618', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/47251-1043-56618-1-real-screen-comics.jpg', '10');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 68019}, {"id": 193308}, {"id": 193310}, {"id": 193311}, {"id": 193373}, {"id": 55075}, {"id": 55076}, {"id": 55082}, {"id": 193309}, {"id": 193312}, {"id": 173152}]', 'NaN', '5', '<p>Funny Frolics ran during 1945 through 1946 for 5 issues. </p>', '1056', 'Funny Frolics', '1945', '92185', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/59190-1056-92185-1-funny-frolics.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 9687}, {"id": 9688}, {"id": 7620}, {"id": 7626}, {"id": 18526}, {"id": 9690}, {"id": 9697}, {"id": 43451}, {"id": 3316}, {"id": 7629}, {"id": 12572}, {"id": 12722}, {"id": 12726}, {"id": 12727}, {"id": 127180}]', 'NaN', '19', '<p>Georgie Comics ran during 1945 through 1948 for 19 issues. This series then continued into <a href="/georgie-and-judy-comics/4050-1266/" data-ref-id="4050-1266"> Georgie And Judy</a>.</p>', '1057', 'Georgie Comics', '1945', '90755', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/57760-1057-90755-1-georgie-comics.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 68019}]', 'NaN', '3', '<p>Krazy Krow ran in 1945 for only 3 issues. </p>', '1059', 'Krazy Krow', '1945', '94895', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/61900-1059-94895-1-krazy-krow.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 5585}, {"id": 9375}, {"id": 178093}, {"id": 9687}, {"id": 68014}, {"id": 169135}, {"id": 7626}, {"id": 7628}, {"id": 7629}, {"id": 18526}, {"id": 7620}, {"id": 9690}, {"id": 12722}, {"id": 12727}, {"id": 12731}, {"id": 15288}, {"id": 40110}, {"id": 68013}, {"id": 3316}]', 'NaN', '36', NULL, '1061', 'Nellie the Nurse', '1945', '90545', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/57550-1061-90545-1-nellie-the-nurse.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 3316}, {"id": 12722}, {"id": 12726}, {"id": 12727}, {"id": 12730}, {"id": 12731}, {"id": 9687}, {"id": 7620}, {"id": 43451}, {"id": 9690}, {"id": 12737}, {"id": 12725}, {"id": 127180}, {"id": 12739}, {"id": 18526}, {"id": 12733}, {"id": 12729}, {"id": 169135}, {"id": 20012}, {"id": 178125}, {"id": 12742}, {"id": 12741}, {"id": 12740}, {"id": 12735}, {"id": 12734}, {"id": 12728}, {"id": 12724}, {"id": 12723}, {"id": 9697}, {"id": 7626}, {"id": 5585}]', '[{"id": 56090}]', '124', '<p>Patsy Walker, a romance character who first appeared in 1944, got her own solo title only months later. Starting in 1945 as an original Timely Golden Age comic, the very popular Patsy Walker ran through 1965 for 124 issues. Although Patsy had always starred in romance and humor comics up until that point, in 1965 (the same year her ongoing ended) she was first incorporated into the Marvel Universe in <a href="/fantastic-four-annual/4050-2129/" data-ref-id="4050-2129">Fantastic Four Annual</a> #3. However, it would be another eleven years before she first appeared as "Hellcat", her super-heroine persona in the modern-day Marvel canon.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-august-1961-omnibus/4050-138275/">Marvel: August 1961 Omnibus</a> (#97)</li></ul>', '1062', 'Patsy Walker', '1945', '141000', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/9116/1995068-1.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 55075}, {"id": 55076}, {"id": 55068}, {"id": 55082}, {"id": 68019}]', 'NaN', '7', '<p>Silly Tunes was one of several Golden Age anthologies published by Timely featuring anthropomorphic characters such as Silly Seal, Ziggy Pig, Super Rabbit and Krazy Krow who were all simultaneously appearing in their own comics. The series lasted for seven issues over the course of two years until it ended in 1947.</p>', '1063', 'Silly Tunes', '1945', '91238', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/58243-1063-91238-1-silly-tunes.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 2356}, {"id": 2350}, {"id": 10935}, {"id": 175516}, {"id": 170063}, {"id": 6263}, {"id": 19145}, {"id": 174632}, {"id": 174411}, {"id": 2365}, {"id": 174412}, {"id": 168081}, {"id": 30886}, {"id": 36441}, {"id": 68176}, {"id": 54347}, {"id": 6268}, {"id": 40252}, {"id": 173077}, {"id": 173556}, {"id": 173809}, {"id": 173810}, {"id": 34766}, {"id": 52973}, {"id": 54348}, {"id": 40250}, {"id": 40251}, {"id": 40249}, {"id": 40293}, {"id": 184918}, {"id": 36494}, {"id": 174234}, {"id": 104140}, {"id": 21096}, {"id": 185603}, {"id": 21095}, {"id": 13473}, {"id": 9793}, {"id": 9336}, {"id": 4916}, {"id": 178656}, {"id": 179174}, {"id": 179618}, {"id": 180562}, {"id": 180613}, {"id": 182715}, {"id": 182716}, {"id": 182832}, {"id": 77593}, {"id": 40279}, {"id": 40118}, {"id": 39132}, {"id": 55703}, {"id": 33378}, {"id": 74560}, {"id": 77477}, {"id": 77583}, {"id": 24665}, {"id": 78973}, {"id": 95805}, {"id": 104139}, {"id": 139125}, {"id": 30888}, {"id": 30887}, {"id": 26147}]', 'NaN', '89', '<p><a href="/marvel-family/4060-19240/" data-ref-id="4060-19240">The Marvel Family</a> is a term that has been attached to the family of characters similar in appearance and powers to the original <a href="/captain-marvel/4005-2350/" data-ref-id="4005-2350">Captain Marvel</a> (this group primarily consists of Mary Marvel, Freddy Freeman and of course Captain Marvel), a character that first appeared in Fawcett''s Whiz Comics. About five years after his first appearance, and a few years after the other "Marvel Family" character''s premieres, the Marvel Family volume was born (December, 1945). Since Captain Marvel was (at the time) the top-selling comic out there, it was no surprise that the Marvel Family series also had some success and it lasted for a little over eight years but ended with a total of 89 issues (January, 1954).</p><h4>Reprints (single issues)</h4><ul><li><a href="/marvel-family/4050-113123/" data-ref-id="4050-113123">Marvel Family</a> (#1-6)</li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1092-the-complete-marvel-famil/4000-681469/">The Complete Marvel Family: Volume 1</a> (#1-6)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-2045-the-kurt-schaffenberger-m/4000-680795/">The Kurt Schaffenberger Marvel Family Collection: Volume 1</a> (#16-40)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-2065-the-kurt-schaffenberger-m/4000-680756/">The Kurt Schaffenberger Marvel Family Collection: Volume 2</a> (#41-64)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-2088-the-kurt-schaffenberger-m/4000-680542/">The Kurt Schaffenberger Marvel Family Collection: Volume 3</a> (#65-89)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1266-the-marvel-family-vs-the-/4000-680750/">The Marvel Family Vs. The Sivana Family: A Golden Age Family Feud</a> (#16, 23, 68, 75 and 84)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/shazam-anthologie/4050-118885/">Shazam! Anthologie</a> (#1) (German)</li></ul>', '1066', 'The Marvel Family', '1945', '119538', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/9116/251573-1066-119538-1-marvel-family-the.jpg', '34');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 1365}, {"id": 97879}, {"id": 97880}, {"id": 97911}, {"id": 16890}, {"id": 98167}, {"id": 98168}, {"id": 98207}, {"id": 98208}, {"id": 98166}, {"id": 98231}, {"id": 98232}, {"id": 98234}, {"id": 98239}, {"id": 98240}, {"id": 98241}, {"id": 98244}, {"id": 98308}, {"id": 98306}, {"id": 98307}, {"id": 98120}, {"id": 98309}, {"id": 98310}, {"id": 98311}, {"id": 98312}, {"id": 98313}, {"id": 98328}, {"id": 98330}, {"id": 98331}, {"id": 98332}, {"id": 98357}, {"id": 98359}, {"id": 173274}, {"id": 97909}, {"id": 9236}, {"id": 19202}, {"id": 27871}, {"id": 30532}, {"id": 97873}, {"id": 97874}, {"id": 97897}, {"id": 97898}, {"id": 97899}, {"id": 97900}, {"id": 97901}, {"id": 97903}, {"id": 97904}, {"id": 98144}, {"id": 97910}, {"id": 97917}, {"id": 97918}, {"id": 97924}, {"id": 97927}, {"id": 97945}, {"id": 97948}, {"id": 97949}, {"id": 97950}, {"id": 97951}, {"id": 98119}, {"id": 98121}, {"id": 98122}]', '[{"id": 55883}]', '76', '<p>Issue #1 published as <a href="/jungle-girl/4050-38373/" data-ref-id="4050-38373">Jungle Girl</a>.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1980-nyoka-the-jungle-girl-vol/4000-682250/">Nyoka, the Jungle Girl - Volume 6</a> (#26-30)</li></ul>', '1068', 'Nyoka the Jungle Girl', '1945', '136093', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/77/509146-425_4_002.jpg', '34');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 1432}, {"id": 30639}, {"id": 79221}, {"id": 79222}, {"id": 10687}, {"id": 30675}, {"id": 74240}, {"id": 118606}, {"id": 47056}, {"id": 9749}, {"id": 96007}, {"id": 92519}, {"id": 111712}, {"id": 111710}, {"id": 111709}, {"id": 111711}, {"id": 90362}, {"id": 81615}, {"id": 74252}, {"id": 74255}, {"id": 74254}, {"id": 74253}, {"id": 74251}, {"id": 74248}, {"id": 63206}, {"id": 61309}, {"id": 19847}, {"id": 17414}, {"id": 12112}, {"id": 1838}]', 'NaN', '89', '<h4>Publishing History</h4><ul><li><a href="/air-fighters-comics/4050-18931/" data-ref-id="4050-18931">Air Fighters Comics</a> (Volume 1, #1-12)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/air-fighters-comics/4050-143697/" data-ref-id="4050-143697">Air Fighters Comics</a> (Volume 2, #1-10)</li><li>Airboy Comics (#23-111)</li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1375-the-complete-airboy-volum/4000-681690/">The Complete Airboy: Volume 4</a> (#54-69)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1391-the-complete-airboy-volum/4000-681702/">The Complete Airboy: Volume 5</a> (#70-85)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-5-the-heap/4000-680896/">The Heap</a> (TH stories)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gwandanaland-comics-1411-simon-and-kirbys-link-tho/4000-681729/">Simon &amp; Kirby''s "Link Thorne: The Flying Fool" Stories</a> (LTFF stories)</li></ul><h4>Notes</h4><ul><li>Indicia for first issue of Airboy Comics calls it vol 2 #11, making it issue #23 in numbering sequence.</li><li>Last issue of Airboy Comics was #111 (vol 10, #4), May 1953.</li></ul>', '1069', 'Airboy Comics', '1945', '168965', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/2/27783/938023-airboy_11.jpg', '37');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 29642}, {"id": 19192}, {"id": 129311}]', 'NaN', '12', '<p>Treasure Comics was an anthology series from Prize Comics, published from 1945-1947, it commonly featured stories including Paul Bunyan, Arabian Knight, Marco Polo, Dr. Styx and The Treasure Keeper.</p>', '1071', 'Treasure Comics', '1945', '94734', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/61739-1071-94734-1-treasure-comics.jpg', '45');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 27941}, {"id": 67904}, {"id": 31595}, {"id": 16890}, {"id": 9634}, {"id": 39872}, {"id": 6005}, {"id": 38594}, {"id": 30943}, {"id": 107623}, {"id": 36190}, {"id": 32775}, {"id": 38634}, {"id": 38662}, {"id": 38991}, {"id": 32248}, {"id": 39021}, {"id": 28392}, {"id": 39873}, {"id": 40110}, {"id": 44016}, {"id": 47650}, {"id": 63244}, {"id": 73232}, {"id": 177932}, {"id": 160345}, {"id": 104920}, {"id": 103398}, {"id": 97322}, {"id": 80212}, {"id": 76710}, {"id": 73253}, {"id": 53218}, {"id": 73230}, {"id": 73032}, {"id": 72194}, {"id": 69778}, {"id": 68094}, {"id": 67377}, {"id": 66182}, {"id": 20401}, {"id": 4000}, {"id": 6175}, {"id": 6128}, {"id": 6125}, {"id": 6124}, {"id": 4936}, {"id": 4885}, {"id": 4537}, {"id": 4534}, {"id": 4003}, {"id": 9605}, {"id": 3940}, {"id": 3924}, {"id": 3099}, {"id": 2611}, {"id": 2395}, {"id": 2048}, {"id": 1702}, {"id": 1699}, {"id": 18136}, {"id": 1691}, {"id": 20399}, {"id": 20391}, {"id": 20333}, {"id": 20002}, {"id": 19759}, {"id": 19202}, {"id": 19144}, {"id": 27436}, {"id": 18080}, {"id": 16277}, {"id": 15864}, {"id": 14131}, {"id": 12802}, {"id": 11798}, {"id": 11399}, {"id": 9622}]', 'NaN', '21', '<p> <em>Real Fact Comics</em> was an anthology series composed of short graphic and prose stories which purported to outline the "real facts" behind many famous individuals. Highlights include: The controversial article crediting <a href="/bob-kane/4040-19137/" data-ref-id="4040-19137"><strong>Bob Kane</strong></a> with the sole creation of <a href="/batman/4005-1699/" data-ref-id="4005-1699"><strong>Batman</strong></a>, <a href="/dick-grayson/4005-1691/" data-ref-id="4005-1691"><strong>Robin</strong></a> and <a href="/joker/4005-1702/" data-ref-id="4005-1702"><strong>The Joker</strong></a>, The first published written work from <a href="/harlan-ellison/4040-45706/" data-ref-id="4040-45706"><strong>Harlan Ellison</strong></a>, and the introduction of <a href="/tommy-tomorrow/4005-27941/" data-ref-id="4005-27941"><strong>Tommy Tomorrow</strong></a>.</p>', '1097', 'Real Fact Comics', '1946', '97929', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/64932-1097-97929-1-real-fact-comics.jpg', '10');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 22169}, {"id": 1946}, {"id": 40199}, {"id": 1947}, {"id": 39641}, {"id": 40201}, {"id": 40200}, {"id": 39813}, {"id": 39812}, {"id": 7286}, {"id": 7287}, {"id": 39814}, {"id": 39739}, {"id": 39740}, {"id": 39288}, {"id": 39816}, {"id": 168239}, {"id": 39817}, {"id": 55598}, {"id": 39644}, {"id": 39858}, {"id": 22143}, {"id": 21155}, {"id": 173757}, {"id": 39642}, {"id": 39492}, {"id": 16648}, {"id": 54136}, {"id": 55070}]', 'NaN', '180', '<p>Issues #65-108 are indexed in "<a data-ref-id="4050-26479" href="/new-funnies/4050-26479/" slug="new-funnies"> New Funnies</a>" </p>', '1098', 'Walter Lantz New Funnies', '1946', '166078', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/3125/903874-wlnf109.jpg', '4');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 2843}, {"id": 2839}, {"id": 2840}, {"id": 1728}, {"id": 7001}, {"id": 7007}, {"id": 1737}, {"id": 4063}, {"id": 2012}, {"id": 1741}, {"id": 2015}, {"id": 60984}, {"id": 4052}, {"id": 2773}, {"id": 1722}, {"id": 2010}, {"id": 2794}, {"id": 4045}, {"id": 1739}, {"id": 2796}, {"id": 1985}, {"id": 1986}, {"id": 1748}, {"id": 1959}, {"id": 7027}, {"id": 1721}, {"id": 1743}, {"id": 1958}, {"id": 120872}, {"id": 1964}, {"id": 1744}, {"id": 1746}, {"id": 1724}, {"id": 1708}, {"id": 56903}, {"id": 1723}, {"id": 1965}, {"id": 160091}, {"id": 83269}, {"id": 83260}, {"id": 83454}, {"id": 83112}, {"id": 82499}, {"id": 82454}, {"id": 160318}, {"id": 60757}, {"id": 60748}, {"id": 60731}, {"id": 38980}, {"id": 22143}, {"id": 2841}, {"id": 2816}, {"id": 1968}, {"id": 1960}]', 'NaN', '301', '<h4>Publication History</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/special-comics/4050-27315/">Special Comics</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/hangman-comics/4050-19580/" data-ref-id="4050-19580">Hangman Comics</a> (#2-8)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/black-hood-comics/4050-19398/">Black Hood Comics</a> (#9-19)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/laugh-comics/4050-22928/">Laugh Comics</a> (#20-99)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/laugh/4050-1101/">Laugh</a> (100-400)</li></ul>', '1101', 'Laugh', '1959', '286678', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/9116/1965127-100.jpg', '101');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 7620}, {"id": 127180}, {"id": 9687}, {"id": 43451}, {"id": 127226}, {"id": 190902}]', 'NaN', '8', '<p>Continued from <a data-ref-id="4050-30471" href="/movie-tunes-comics/4050-30471/" slug="movie-tunes-comics">  Movie Tunes Comics</a>, Frankie Comics ran during 1946 through 1949 for 8 issues. This series then continued back into <a data-ref-id="4050-1197" href="/frankie-and-lana/4050-1197/" slug="frankie-and-lana"> Frankie And Lana</a>. </p>', '1111', 'Frankie Comics', '1946', '90352', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/5/54649/1133040-851_o_1_.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 7620}, {"id": 169135}, {"id": 3316}, {"id": 9690}, {"id": 12726}, {"id": 12722}, {"id": 12730}, {"id": 43451}, {"id": 68014}]', 'NaN', '15', '<p>Continued from <a data-ref-id="4050-944" href="/comedy-comics/4050-944/" slug="comedy-comics">   Comedy Comics</a>, Margie Comics ran during 1946 through 1949 for 15 issues. This series then continued into <a data-ref-id="4050-30598" href="/reno-browne-hollywoods-greatest-cowgirl/4050-30598/" slug="reno-browne-hollywoods-greatest-cowgirl">  Reno Browne, Hollywood''s Greatest Cowgirl</a>. </p>', '1113', 'Margie Comics', '1946', '95131', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/62136-1113-95131-1-margie-comics.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 39433}, {"id": 3104}, {"id": 3105}, {"id": 1951}, {"id": 1950}, {"id": 163681}, {"id": 64424}, {"id": 123200}, {"id": 85847}, {"id": 85130}, {"id": 39434}, {"id": 81865}, {"id": 82002}, {"id": 167296}, {"id": 167327}, {"id": 184356}, {"id": 21010}, {"id": 55081}, {"id": 4581}, {"id": 52432}, {"id": 167363}, {"id": 7264}, {"id": 9826}, {"id": 38599}, {"id": 39780}, {"id": 26147}, {"id": 114172}, {"id": 114173}, {"id": 18738}, {"id": 16852}, {"id": 167328}, {"id": 70036}, {"id": 171377}, {"id": 173159}, {"id": 173160}, {"id": 68019}]', 'NaN', '71', '<p>The first four issues were published by Timely, afterwards the series was switched over to the publisher, St. John, then to Pines.</p>', '1114', 'Paul Terry''s Mighty Mouse Comics', '1946', '95200', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/62205-1114-95200-1-mighty-mouse.jpg', '2043');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 55075}, {"id": 55076}, {"id": 55068}]', 'NaN', '4', '<p>Continued from <a href="/dopey-duck/4050-30506/" data-ref-id="4050-30506"> Dopey Duck</a>, Wacky Duck ran during 1946 through 1947 for 4 issues. This series then changed themes dramatically and was re-named with issue 7 as <a href="/justice-comics/4050-57134/" data-ref-id="4050-57134"> Justice Comics</a>.</p>', '1116', 'Wacky Duck', '1946', '57668', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/48206-1116-57668-1-wacky-duck.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 127180}, {"id": 127226}, {"id": 7620}, {"id": 9690}, {"id": 5585}, {"id": 9687}, {"id": 43451}, {"id": 7626}, {"id": 7629}, {"id": 9375}, {"id": 18526}, {"id": 178093}]', 'NaN', '15', '<p>Continued from <a data-ref-id="4050-1007" href="/ideal-comics/4050-1007/" slug="ideal-comics">  Ideal Comics</a>, Willie Comics ran during 1946 through 1949 for 15 issues. This series then continued into <a data-ref-id="4050-30510" href="/lil-willie-comics/4050-30510/" slug="lil-willie-comics"> Li''l Willie Comics</a>. </p>', '1117', 'Willie Comics', '1946', '91014', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/5/54649/1173145-4675_o_1_.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 34149}]', 'NaN', '3', NULL, '1119', 'Blackstone, Master Magician Comics', '1946', '173410', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/9116/974304-1.jpg', '3139');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 18142}, {"id": 16890}, {"id": 160345}, {"id": 1807}, {"id": 18060}, {"id": 175362}, {"id": 91860}, {"id": 62676}, {"id": 47460}, {"id": 47403}, {"id": 23539}, {"id": 16462}, {"id": 16450}, {"id": 16368}, {"id": 16363}, {"id": 16246}, {"id": 9992}]', 'NaN', '79', '<p>.</p>', '1133', 'A Date with Judy', '1947', '53209', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/45860-1133-53209-1-date-with-judy-a.jpg', '10');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 1807}, {"id": 51046}, {"id": 16890}, {"id": 18060}, {"id": 63266}]', '[{"id": 44795}, {"id": 57596}]', '67', '<p>DC hoped it could beat slumping sales with its first entry into the crime comics genre. To minimize risk, DC licensed an established property - the Gang Busters radio program, which had been on the air waves since 1935 (originally under the name of the G-Men). Edited by Jack Schiff, the Gang Busters comic focused on FBI cases and stand alone crime stories. The first issue included tales such as "Murder was my business" and "The case of the Iron-clad alibi." Later issues featured photo covers, a practice becoming increasingly common in the late 1940''s.</p>', '1134', 'Gang Busters', '1947', '157130', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/2/27783/797909-gangbusters_a.jpg', '10');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 9203}, {"id": 6735}, {"id": 9207}, {"id": 9233}, {"id": 52832}, {"id": 16890}, {"id": 65322}]', '[{"id": 57252}, {"id": 58592}]', '24', '<p>Series continued from: Boy Explorers Comics (Harvey/Family Comics, 1946) #2</p><p>Series continues as: Terry and the Pirates (Charlton, 1955) #26 (each series has a #26 issue).</p>', '1139', 'Terry and the Pirates Comics', '1947', '96955', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/63959-1139-96955-1-terry-and-the-pirate.jpg', '20');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 43451}, {"id": 7620}, {"id": 3316}, {"id": 12727}, {"id": 12730}, {"id": 12726}, {"id": 12731}, {"id": 68013}, {"id": 9375}, {"id": 9687}, {"id": 12722}, {"id": 12739}, {"id": 15288}, {"id": 18526}, {"id": 68014}]', 'NaN', '12', '<p>Numbered 27 to 38 for a total of 12 issues. Series continued from <a data-ref-id="4050-946" href="/krazy-komics/4050-946/" slug="krazy-komics">   Krazy Komics</a> and continues into <a data-ref-id="4050-1346" href="/cindy-smith/4050-1346/" slug="cindy-smith">   Cindy Smith</a>.</p>', '1141', 'Cindy Comics', '1947', '90603', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/57608-1141-90603-1-cindy-comics.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 68014}, {"id": 9375}, {"id": 178093}, {"id": 7626}, {"id": 18526}, {"id": 7629}, {"id": 7628}, {"id": 120874}, {"id": 127180}, {"id": 169135}]', 'NaN', '14', '<p>Continued from <a data-ref-id="4050-18581" href="/all-winners-comics/4050-18581/" slug="all-winners-comics">  All Winners Comics</a>, Hedy De Vine Comics ran during 1947 through 1949 for 14 issues. This series then continued into <a data-ref-id="4050-1353" href="/hedy-of-hollywood-comics/4050-1353/" slug="hedy-of-hollywood-comics"> Hedy Of Hollywood Comics</a>. </p>', '1142', 'Hedy De Vine Comics', '1947', '187936', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1/15776/8705141-hedy22a.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 9690}, {"id": 127180}, {"id": 43451}, {"id": 7620}, {"id": 9687}, {"id": 3316}, {"id": 12726}, {"id": 12730}]', 'NaN', '15', '<p>Numbering continues from <a href="/all-surprise/4050-972/" data-ref-id="4050-972">All Surprise</a> #1-12, becomes <a href="/cowgirl-romances/4050-30440/" data-ref-id="4050-30440">Cowgirl Romances</a> with issue #28</p>', '1143', 'Jeanie Comics', '1947', '93076', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/60081-1143-93076-1-jeanie-comics.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 98468}]', 'NaN', '41', '<p>Continued from <a href="/justice-comics/4050-57134/" data-ref-id="4050-57134"><em>Justice Comics</em></a>, Justice ran during 1949 through 1955 for 41 issues.</p><p>This series featured crime-themed adventures, in which justice always prevailed. It was continued as <a href="/tales-of-justice/4050-1716/" data-ref-id="4050-1716"> Tales Of Justice </a>with issue 53.</p>', '1144', 'Justice', '1949', '90926', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/57928-1144-90923-1-justice.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 77092}]', 'NaN', '237', '<p><strong>Proper Japanese Title</strong>: 別冊ビッグコミック</p><p>Bessatsu Big Comic began in 1971 as the second ongoing special issue of <a href="/big-comic/4050-90466/" data-ref-id="4050-90466">Big Comic</a>, taking over some aspects of the first special issue (<a href="/big-comic-zokan/4050-141598/" data-ref-id="4050-141598">Big Comic Zōkan</a>). As was industry standard for major manga magazines at the time, special issues were often used to collect and reprint chapters of popular works while also publishing some minor original material. Big Comic Zōkan''s first five issues all served this direct role (primarily being collected reprints of <a href="/golgo-13/4050-61493/" data-ref-id="4050-61493">Golgo 13</a>) but Bessatsu was then created to be a dedicated magazine for this while Zōkan began focusing more on original material.</p><p>Initially Bessatsu Big Comic reprinted ongoing Big Comic serials from several authors (<a href="/sasori/4050-107392/" data-ref-id="4050-107392">Sasori</a>, Golgo 13, <a href="/sabu-to-ichi-torimono-hikae/4050-41033/" data-ref-id="4050-41033">Sabu to Ichi</a>, <a href="/notari-matsutaro/4050-102345/" data-ref-id="4050-102345">Notari Matsutarō</a>, Mikiya Mochizuki) but in 1976 it fully became a vehicle for reprinting Golgo 13 and as such it is often associated solely with Golgo 13. Although reprinting Golgo 13 is the primary focus, other authors have appeared with original material in these issues including the first published work by <a href="/naoki-urasawa/4040-58221/" data-ref-id="4040-58221">Naoki Urasawa</a>.</p><p>Notably, the existence of Bessatsu magazines to collect and reprint material from the parent magazine was a trend that mostly died out through the 70''s but Bessatsu Big Comic survived into the modern day. This is due to the nature of Golgo 13 (one of the best-selling and longest-running manga of all time) itself, as collected chapters are published here years before they are available through the standard tankobon format. In a sense these serve as Shogakukan''s collections of Golgo 13 (as the company that publishes the serialization) while the author''s own company Leed releases the actual tankobon and bunko editions that remain in print.</p>', '1146', 'Bessatsu Big Comic', '1971', '1025968', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/11158/111586530/9140440-19710401.jpg', '2781');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 169135}, {"id": 7626}, {"id": 9375}, {"id": 18526}, {"id": 7629}, {"id": 68014}, {"id": 178125}, {"id": 7628}, {"id": 9376}, {"id": 74205}]', 'NaN', '9', '<p>Continued from <a data-ref-id="4050-30461" href="/kid-movie-komics/4050-30461/" slug="kid-movie-komics">  Kid Movie Komics</a>, Rusty Comics ran during 1947 through 1949 for 9 issues. This series then continued into <a data-ref-id="4050-1293" href="/rusty-and-her-family/4050-1293/" slug="rusty-and-her-family"> Rusty And Her Family</a>. </p>', '1147', 'Rusty Comics', '1947', '91267', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/11/110017/8744440-rusty_comics_012_001.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 3316}, {"id": 12726}, {"id": 12727}, {"id": 43451}, {"id": 9687}, {"id": 12722}, {"id": 12730}, {"id": 12731}, {"id": 7620}, {"id": 9688}, {"id": 127180}, {"id": 9375}, {"id": 68013}, {"id": 127226}, {"id": 178125}]', 'NaN', '15', '<p>Continued from <a data-ref-id="4050-22987" href="/all-teen/4050-22987/" slug="all-teen">  All Teen</a>, Teen Comics ran during 1947 through 1950 for 15 issues. This series then continued into <a data-ref-id="4050-1427" href="/journey-into-unknown-worlds/4050-1427/" slug="journey-into-unknown-worlds"> Journey Into Unknown Worlds</a>. </p>', '1148', 'Teen Comics', '1947', '57327', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/5/54649/1062859-teen_comics_21.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 3948}, {"id": 169766}]', 'NaN', '92', '<p>Issue #v7#5 has #60 on the cover, when it should have had #59. To correct this misnumbering, issue #v7#6 has 60A on the cover.</p>', '1151', 'Justice Traps the Guilty', '1947', '93818', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/60823-1151-93818-1-justice-traps-the-gu.jpg', '45');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 5151}, {"id": 83667}, {"id": 83668}, {"id": 110274}, {"id": 179276}]', 'NaN', '11', '<p>Issues #13 and 14 are in the <a href="/a-1-comics/4050-1032/" data-ref-id="4050-1032"><em>A-1 Comics</em></a> volume.</p>', '1153', 'Manhunt', '1947', '105257', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/72259-1153-105257-1-manhunt.jpg', '84');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 16363}, {"id": 16444}, {"id": 16246}, {"id": 16462}, {"id": 16450}, {"id": 9992}, {"id": 16453}, {"id": 16463}, {"id": 16441}, {"id": 18142}, {"id": 16459}, {"id": 47403}, {"id": 16448}, {"id": 16368}, {"id": 1807}, {"id": 16457}, {"id": 47460}, {"id": 90520}, {"id": 91860}, {"id": 156621}, {"id": 31120}, {"id": 16461}, {"id": 16367}, {"id": 2048}]', 'NaN', '71', '<p>Another teen title joined DC''s lineup. Leave it to Binky centered on the hapless Binky Biggs and his efforts to date the beautiful Peggy, despite the interferences of his troublemaking younger brother "Little Allergy." Edited by Sheldon Mayer with art by Bob Oksner, Leave it to Binky followed in the footsteps of DC''s 1944 launch of the teen title Buzzy. Both titles reflected the fact that competitor Archie Comics had turned teen comics into big business through its popular freckle faced hero.</p>', '1168', 'Leave it to Binky', '1948', '56353', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/47008-1168-56353-1-leave-it-to-binky.jpg', '10');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 91721}, {"id": 51046}, {"id": 1807}]', 'NaN', '67', '<p>Like its contemporary, Gang Busters, the crime comic Mr District Attorney was licensed from a popular radio show. The radio version had been on air since 1939 and DC was quick to advertise its popular pedigree with a cover banner reading, "Based on radio''s #1 hit!" Its subject was the tough talking (and nameless) District Attorney, an implacable and callous force for justice who fought ugly and amoral crooks with colorful names like, "Smoke-rings" Thomson and teh Pittsburgh Kid. Mr District Attorney came along at the right time to catch a wave of crime comics and lasted for 67 issues.</p>', '1169', 'Mr. District Attorney', '1948', '180160', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/9116/1011212-1.jpg', '10');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 16362}, {"id": 13168}, {"id": 2033}, {"id": 39718}, {"id": 186038}, {"id": 6175}, {"id": 1807}, {"id": 39720}, {"id": 186037}, {"id": 48154}, {"id": 39728}, {"id": 39727}, {"id": 39726}, {"id": 39725}, {"id": 39724}, {"id": 39723}, {"id": 39722}, {"id": 39721}, {"id": 16890}, {"id": 16363}, {"id": 16246}, {"id": 14281}, {"id": 7886}, {"id": 1838}]', 'NaN', '85', '<p>The introduction of <em>Western Comics</em> stood as proof of DC''s commitment to the <a href="/western/4015-56096/" data-ref-id="4015-56096">Western</a> genre. The first issue introduced new characters including the Wyoming Kid, Cowboy Marshal and Rodeo Rick, but the Vigilante may have seemed most familiar. The bandana masked hero had already earned his place among the 7 Soldiers of Victory following his introduction in <a href="/action-comics-42/4000-112189/" data-ref-id="4000-112189"><em>Action Comics #42</em></a> (November 1941), Although his adventures took place in contemporary times, the Vigilante''s costume helped him fit in among the stars of <em>Western Comics</em>.</p>', '1171', 'Western Comics', '1948', '218988', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/2/27783/1261850-westerndc_1.jpg', '10');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 9231}, {"id": 9232}, {"id": 39441}, {"id": 39440}, {"id": 9230}, {"id": 38929}, {"id": 39439}, {"id": 40001}, {"id": 40323}, {"id": 40259}, {"id": 40354}, {"id": 39663}, {"id": 10359}, {"id": 22553}, {"id": 22143}, {"id": 39853}, {"id": 40272}, {"id": 40269}, {"id": 40202}, {"id": 40142}, {"id": 40110}, {"id": 40277}, {"id": 40324}, {"id": 40345}, {"id": 191698}, {"id": 39984}, {"id": 10799}, {"id": 12112}, {"id": 39413}, {"id": 12119}, {"id": 37611}, {"id": 30943}, {"id": 22182}, {"id": 22179}, {"id": 22172}, {"id": 22164}, {"id": 22158}, {"id": 22144}]', '[{"id": 55883}]', '145', '<p>Movie, radio &amp; TV; Clayton Moore starred as Lone Ranger in the movies.  <br/>#1 - 37: strip reprints. </p>', '1172', 'The Lone Ranger', '1948', '116602', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/229/223200-1172-116602-1-lone-ranger-the.jpg', '4');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 32957}, {"id": 51878}, {"id": 9262}, {"id": 51519}, {"id": 103439}, {"id": 83213}, {"id": 12754}, {"id": 66512}, {"id": 20651}, {"id": 103437}, {"id": 75997}, {"id": 95638}, {"id": 141704}, {"id": 110974}, {"id": 103436}, {"id": 110970}, {"id": 66513}, {"id": 141705}, {"id": 88263}, {"id": 51522}, {"id": 110963}, {"id": 51521}, {"id": 173094}, {"id": 66566}, {"id": 51520}, {"id": 20174}, {"id": 134272}, {"id": 174145}, {"id": 31370}, {"id": 19962}, {"id": 173718}, {"id": 100004}, {"id": 173717}, {"id": 175305}, {"id": 141668}, {"id": 154806}, {"id": 114327}, {"id": 66628}, {"id": 89529}, {"id": 66840}, {"id": 66839}, {"id": 9240}, {"id": 66113}, {"id": 38273}, {"id": 21941}, {"id": 18654}, {"id": 17078}, {"id": 16996}, {"id": 16648}, {"id": 13928}, {"id": 9241}]', 'NaN', '168', '<ul><li>#1-65 was published by Dell</li><li>#66-80 was published by Gold Key</li><li>#81-92 was published by King</li><li>#93 - does not exist</li><li>#94-138 was published by Charlton</li><li>#139-171 was published by Gold Key/Whitman (#160 &amp; 161 do not exist)</li></ul>', '1174', 'Popeye', '1948', '2492', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/3125/542739-popeye001.jpg', '178');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 22892}, {"id": 18121}, {"id": 18122}, {"id": 35482}, {"id": 22937}, {"id": 35651}, {"id": 36802}, {"id": 18123}, {"id": 18128}, {"id": 37429}]', '[{"id": 55883}]', '128', '<p>Volume starts with issue #10, with continuing numbering from <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/tarzan/4050-19597/">Tarzan</a>.</p><p>Name changes to <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/edgar-rice-burroughs-tarzan-of-the-apes/4050-1343/">Edgar Rice Burroughs'' Tarzan of the Apes</a> in issue #138.</p><h2>Collected Editions</h2><ul><li><a href="/edgar-rice-burroughs-tarzan-the-jesse-marsh-years-vol-2/4000-272215/" data-ref-id="4000-272215">Edgar Rice Burroughs'' Tarzan: The Jesse Marsh Years Vol. 2</a> (#?)</li><li><a href="/edgar-rice-burroughs-tarzan-the-jesse-marsh-years-vol-3/4000-272216/" data-ref-id="4000-272216">Edgar Rice Burroughs'' Tarzan: The Jesse Marsh Years Vol. 3</a> (#11-16)</li><li><a href="/edgar-rice-burroughs-tarzan-the-jesse-marsh-years-vol-4/4000-272217/" data-ref-id="4000-272217">Edgar Rice Burroughs'' Tarzan: The Jesse Marsh Years Vol. 4</a> (#?)</li><li><a href="/edgar-rice-burroughs-tarzan-the-jesse-marsh-years-vol-5/4000-272218/" data-ref-id="4000-272218">Edgar Rice Burroughs'' Tarzan: The Jesse Marsh Years Vol. 5</a> (#?)</li><li><a href="/edgar-rice-burroughs-tarzan-the-jesse-marsh-years-vol-6/4000-272219/" data-ref-id="4000-272219">Edgar Rice Burroughs'' Tarzan: The Jesse Marsh Years Vol. 6</a> (#28-32)</li><li><a href="/edgar-rice-burroughs-tarzan-the-jesse-marsh-years-vol-7/4000-272220/" data-ref-id="4000-272220">Edgar Rice Burroughs'' Tarzan: The Jesse Marsh Years Vol. 7</a> (#33-38)</li><li><a href="/edgar-rice-burroughs-tarzan-the-jesse-marsh-years-vol-8/4000-272221/" data-ref-id="4000-272221">Edgar Rice Burroughs'' Tarzan: The Jesse Marsh Years Vol. 8</a> (#39-43)</li><li><a href="/edgar-rice-burroughs-tarzan-the-jesse-marsh-years-vol-9/4000-272222/" data-ref-id="4000-272222">Edgar Rice Burroughs'' Tarzan: The Jesse Marsh Years Vol. 9</a> (#44-46)</li><li><a href="/edgar-rice-burroughs-tarzan-the-jesse-marsh-years-vol-10/4000-309483/" data-ref-id="4000-309483">Edgar Rice Burroughs'' Tarzan: The Jesse Marsh Years Vol. 10</a> (#47-51)</li><li><a href="/edgar-rice-burroughs-tarzan-the-jesse-marsh-years-vol-11/4000-344056/" data-ref-id="4000-344056">Edgar Rice Burroughs'' Tarzan: The Jesse Marsh Years Vol. 11</a> (#52-56)</li></ul>', '1176', 'Edgar Rice Burroughs'' Tarzan', '1949', '174548', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/3125/980239-tar10.jpg', '178');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 74279}, {"id": 4220}, {"id": 16890}, {"id": 2652}, {"id": 2716}, {"id": 52832}, {"id": 74280}, {"id": 74281}]', 'NaN', '22', NULL, '1183', 'Humphrey Comics', '1948', '306138', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/3125/2119444-hump1.jpg', '20');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 5132}, {"id": 16229}, {"id": 27699}, {"id": 125553}, {"id": 16890}, {"id": 52832}]', 'NaN', '28', '<p>#1: Published as part of <a href="/a-1-comics/4050-1032/" data-ref-id="4050-1032">A-1 Comics</a> , <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a-1-comics/4050-1032/">A-1 Comics</a> <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a-1-comics-1-kerry-drake/4000-99018/">#1</a>.</p><p>#2-5: Published by Magazine Enterprises, <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/kerry-drake/4050-81922/">Kerry Drake</a>.</p><p>#6-33: Published by Harvey</p>', '1184', 'Kerry Drake Detective Cases', '1948', '94140', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/61145-1184-94140-1-kerry-drake-detectiv.jpg', '20');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 11329}, {"id": 11397}, {"id": 74205}]', 'NaN', '5', '<p>Blaze Carson ran during 1948 through 1949 for 5 issues. This series then continued into <a data-ref-id="4050-1289" href="/rex-hart/4050-1289/" slug="rex-hart"> Rex Hart</a>. </p>', '1192', 'Blaze Carson', '1948', '92175', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/59180-1192-92175-1-blaze-carson.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 18223}, {"id": 35126}, {"id": 73126}, {"id": 73127}, {"id": 73128}, {"id": 73129}, {"id": 75894}, {"id": 75895}]', 'NaN', '1', '<p>Doom Force Special was a one-off parody of comics at the time, published near the height of comic speculation/collecting (the cover is a parody of <a href="/rob-liefeld/4040-5181/" data-ref-id="4040-5181">Rob Liefeld</a>''s artwork). Although it is unlikely there were any actual plans or expectations for this series to continue, at the back of the issue was a list of dozens of characters readers could potentially see if Doom Force ever returned. As this special was written at the same time as Grant Morrison''s highly-successful and acclaimed run on <a href="/doom-patrol/4050-3786/" data-ref-id="4050-3786">Doom Patrol</a> (and even features future versions of two of its cast members), it was collected alongside the rest of his run over a decade later in the final volume, <a href="/doom-patrol-planet-love/4050-27250/" data-ref-id="4050-27250">Doom Patrol: Planet Love</a>.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doom-patrol-3-book-three/4000-589805/" data-ref-id="4000-589805">Doom Patrol Book Three</a></li><li><a href="/doom-patrol-omnibus/4050-76082/" data-ref-id="4050-76082">Doom Patrol Omnibus</a></li></ul>', '1193', 'Doom Force Special', '1992', '165691', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/9116/899276-1.jpg', '10');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 14335}]', 'NaN', '4', '<p>Complete Mystery ran during 1948 through 1949 for 4 issues. This series then continued into <a data-ref-id="4050-1297" href="/true-complete-mystery/4050-1297/" slug="true-complete-mystery"> True Complete Mystery</a>.</p>', '1194', 'Complete Mystery', '1948', '91747', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/58752-1194-91747-1-complete-mystery.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 14131}, {"id": 98468}]', 'NaN', '10', '<p>Crimefighters ran during 1948 through 1949 for 10 issues. This series then continued into <a data-ref-id="4050-1629" href="/crime-fighters/4050-1629/" slug="crime-fighters"> Crime Fighters</a>. </p>', '1196', 'Crimefighters', '1948', '90736', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/57741-1196-90736-1-crimefighters.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 9690}, {"id": 43451}, {"id": 190902}]', 'NaN', '4', '<p>Continued from <a data-ref-id="4050-1111" href="/frankie-comics/4050-1111/" slug="frankie-comics">   Frankie Comics</a>, Frankie And Lana ran during 1948 through 1949 for 4 issues. This series then continued into <a data-ref-id="4050-30508" href="/frankie-fuddle/4050-30508/" slug="frankie-fuddle">  Frankie Fuddle</a>.</p>', '1197', 'Frankie and Lana Comics', '1948', '90360', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/57365-1197-90360-1-frankie-and-lana-com.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 7238}, {"id": 11329}, {"id": 11397}, {"id": 107199}]', 'NaN', '4', '<p><b>Kid Colt: Hero of the West Volume 1</b></p><p><a href="/kid-colt/4005-7238/" data-ref-id="4005-7238">Kid Colt</a> was a Western comic book character who first appeared in this self-titled series. While the first four issues are titled Kid Colt by the indicia, they all feature subtitles on the cover and after issue four the series renamed itself to match the subtitle first adopted by issue three, <a href="/kid-colt-outlaw/4050-1199/" data-ref-id="4050-1199">Kid Colt Outlaw</a>. Under that title the series continued for three full decades until the series finally came to a close after a two hundred and twenty-nine issue run.</p>', '1198', 'Kid Colt', '1948', '94151', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/61156-1198-94151-1-kid-colt-hero-of-th.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 7238}, {"id": 32547}, {"id": 35500}, {"id": 4069}, {"id": 39512}, {"id": 7240}, {"id": 188641}, {"id": 107199}, {"id": 38765}, {"id": 38766}, {"id": 39550}, {"id": 39694}, {"id": 36641}, {"id": 74205}, {"id": 61436}, {"id": 39466}, {"id": 61356}, {"id": 60559}, {"id": 39514}, {"id": 39276}, {"id": 67720}, {"id": 75106}, {"id": 107200}, {"id": 107201}, {"id": 107202}, {"id": 190541}, {"id": 190697}, {"id": 192195}, {"id": 38389}, {"id": 3115}, {"id": 7239}, {"id": 11329}, {"id": 12112}, {"id": 15870}, {"id": 32406}, {"id": 36118}, {"id": 38342}, {"id": 38388}, {"id": 39396}, {"id": 38993}, {"id": 39048}, {"id": 39077}, {"id": 39078}, {"id": 39275}, {"id": 3085}, {"id": 39291}, {"id": 39296}, {"id": 39395}]', 'NaN', '225', '<p><a href="/kid-colt/4005-7238/" data-ref-id="4005-7238">Kid Colt</a> was a Western comic book character dating back to 1948, where he made his first appearance in the comic series <a href="/kid-colt-hero-of-the-west/4050-1198/" data-ref-id="4050-1198"> Kid Colt: Hero of the West</a>. However, aforementioned series didn''t last too long, at least not under its original title as it changed the name of the comic after issue four (although the covers had already begun the name change with issue three). This new title was, <a href="/kid-colt-outlaw/4050-1199/" data-ref-id="4050-1199"> Kid Colt: Outlaw</a> which is what it continued to be three full decades until the series finally came to a close after a two hundred and twenty-nine issue run. That makes Kid Colt the longest-running cowboy star in an American published comic-book , featured in stories for a 31-year stretch from 1948-1979, though from 1966 most of the published stories were reprints.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-august-1961-omnibus/4050-138275/">Marvel: August 1961 Omnibus</a> (#101)</li></ul>', '1199', 'Kid Colt Outlaw', '1949', '98550', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/65553-1199-98550-1-kid-colt-outlaw.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 5585}, {"id": 7626}, {"id": 18526}, {"id": 179650}, {"id": 7629}, {"id": 7628}, {"id": 169135}, {"id": 16890}, {"id": 37485}, {"id": 169250}, {"id": 178174}]', 'NaN', '7', '<p>Lana ran during 1948 through 1949 for 7 issues. This series then continued into <a href="/little-lana/4050-30511/" data-ref-id="4050-30511"> Little Lana</a>.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-venus-1-volume-1/4000-372840/" data-ref-id="4000-372840">Marvel Masterworks: Atlas Era: Venus Volume 1</a> (#4)</li></ul>', '1201', 'Lana', '1948', '94914', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/61919-1201-94914-1-lana-comics.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('NaN', 'NaN', '10', '<p>Lawbreakers Always Lose ran during 1948 through 1949 for 10 issues. </p>', '1202', 'Lawbreakers Always Lose', '1948', '94923', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/61928-1202-94923-1-lawbreakers-always-l.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('NaN', 'NaN', '2', '<p>Wacky Duck ran in 1948 for only 2 issues. </p>', '1211', 'Wacky Duck', '1948', '57672', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/5/54649/1061904-wacky_duck_1.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 7238}, {"id": 32547}, {"id": 7237}, {"id": 88519}, {"id": 143558}, {"id": 107199}, {"id": 74205}, {"id": 37793}, {"id": 22741}, {"id": 11397}, {"id": 143601}, {"id": 40147}, {"id": 143602}, {"id": 11329}, {"id": 23358}, {"id": 194398}, {"id": 143603}, {"id": 194401}, {"id": 194400}, {"id": 194399}, {"id": 67719}, {"id": 56382}, {"id": 40110}, {"id": 11440}, {"id": 143557}, {"id": 1838}, {"id": 192135}, {"id": 39694}, {"id": 32725}, {"id": 22740}, {"id": 194863}, {"id": 195783}]', 'NaN', '55', '<p>The first two issues of the series where named <a href="../../wild-west/49-22232/" rel="nofollow ">  Wild West</a>, it became Wild Western with issue 3.</p>', '1213', 'Wild Western', '1948', '188727', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/5/54649/1064400-wild_western_3.jpg', '31');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 9444}, {"id": 9445}]', 'NaN', '9', '<h4>Publishing History</h4><ul><li>(#1-5) <strong>Charlie Chan</strong> [Jun, 1948 Prize]</li><li>(#6-9) <strong>All-New Mystery Adventures of Charlie Chan</strong> [Dec, 1948 Charlton]</li><li>(#10-11) <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/zaza-the-mystic/4050-36845/">Zaza the Mystic</a> [Apr, 1956]</li><li>(#12-16) <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/this-magazine-is-haunted/4050-36770/">This Magazine is Haunted</a> [Jul, 1957]</li><li>(#17-25) <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/outer-space/4050-1862/">Outer Space</a> [May, 1958]</li></ul>', '1219', 'Charlie Chan', '1948', '91667', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/58672-1219-91667-1-charlie-chan.jpg', '45');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 1345}, {"id": 5652}, {"id": 12112}, {"id": 47989}, {"id": 32725}, {"id": 179288}, {"id": 3085}, {"id": 39296}, {"id": 39694}, {"id": 76858}, {"id": 103998}, {"id": 177150}, {"id": 183333}, {"id": 183334}]', '[{"id": 56040}]', '38', '<p>Issues 1 - 3 are part of the <a href="/a-1-comics/4050-1032/" data-ref-id="4050-1032">A-1 comics</a> series.</p><p>The Tim Holt series continues in <a href="/red-mask/4050-27105/" data-ref-id="4050-27105">Red Mask</a> #42-54.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li>The Original Ghost Rider Vol. 1 (#12-14)</li></ul>', '1223', 'Tim Holt', '1948', '98468', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1/15776/8677826-timholt4a.jpg', '84');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('NaN', 'NaN', '5', NULL, '1239', 'Ozzie and Harriet', '1949', '53062', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/45721-1239-53062-1-ozzie-and-harriet.jpg', '10');
INSERT INTO volumes (characters, concepts, count_of_issues, description, id, name, start_year, first_issue.id, image.screen_url, publisher.id) VALUES ('[{"id": 134159}, {"id": 150379}, {"id": 129144}, {"id": 129143}, {"id": 150367}, {"id": 135834}, {"id": 150353}, {"id": 150354}, {"id": 150356}, {"id": 150360}, {"id": 150361}, {"id": 150364}, {"id": 129158}, {"id": 150368}, {"id": 150373}, {"id": 150374}, {"id": 150375}, {"id": 150376}, {"id": 150377}, {"id": 150378}, {"id": 150380}, {"id": 150396}, {"id": 40142}, {"id": 8485}, {"id": 16890}, {"id": 18060}, {"id": 18080}, {"id": 19196}, {"id": 28392}, {"id": 29649}, {"id": 30220}, {"id": 36268}, {"id": 129174}, {"id": 63266}, {"id": 104921}, {"id": 112809}, {"id": 112811}, {"id": 129095}, {"id": 129122}, {"id": 129145}, {"id": 2906}]', '[{"id": 55883}]', '9', '<p>An odd entry into the field of celebrity comics, this title featured Miss Beverly Hills and her interactions with real life Hollywood guest stars including Alan Ladd and Wanda Hendrix. Beverly had a newspaper reporter boyfriend named Will Shire (A play on LA''s Wilshire Boulevard) and most stories revolved around her desire to meet movie stars and become a star herself. The series blended the celebrity, humor and romance genres with mixed results and sadly the title only made 9 issues. However Beverly did make a brief return as a backup feature in four issues of The Adventures of Bob Hope.</p>', '1241', 'Miss Beverly Hills of Hollywood', '1949', '56459', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/0/4/47099-1241-56459-1-miss-beverly-hills-o.jpg', '10');
